  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6823.8 sitting below the 6847 GEX flip in PIN regime, dealers are currently net buying the dip as they hedge their long gamma positions, creating stabilizing flow that should cap downside momentum. The massive +5991.7M gamma wall at 6900 represents heavy dealer selling pressure that will act as strong resistance, while the structure shows dealers will increasingly buy any weakness toward the 6700 negative gamma zone. Key levels to watch are the 6847 flip strike (regime change point) and the 6850-6900 zone where three major positive gamma walls create a significant resistance cluster.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect price to grind higher toward 6850-6900 but face heavy selling pressure in that zone.",
